<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-07T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-07T22:00:00-05:00" n="476" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12511: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-08T11:00:00+08:00">November 8, 1933—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 7—11:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>841. Following from Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“November 7, 5 p.m. I have received information believed to be
                                    reliable that the anti-communist campaign in Kiangsi was
                                    abandoned November 5th. Reason assigned by my informant was
                                    pro-communist sentiment among Government troops and general
                                    unwillingness to fight.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>